# Rust-Only Code Generation

This rule ensures that only Rust code is generated by Cursor.

<rule>
name: rust_only_code
description: Enforces Rust-only code generation
filters:
  - type: event
    pattern: "code_generation"

actions:
  - type: reject
    conditions:
      - pattern: "(?i)python|javascript|typescript|java|cpp|c\\+\\+|go|php|ruby|swift|kotlin|scala"
        message: "Only Rust code generation is allowed in this project"
  
  - type: suggest
    message: |
      Please ensure:
      1. All code generation is in Rust
      2. Use standard Rust idioms and patterns
      3. Follow Rust best practices for error handling and memory safety

examples:
  - input: |
      # Bad: Python code
      def hello_world():
          print("Hello, World!")
      
      # Good: Rust code
      fn hello_world() {
          println!("Hello, World!");
      }
    output: "Use Rust code instead of Python"

metadata:
  priority: high
  version: 1.0
</rule>